                        modern sophists, includ<pc>-</pc>
                        <lb/>ing such theses as <rs type="title">Comme Quoi <rs type="name"
                                key="P12">Napoléon</rs></rs>)<lb/>(See whether some idea can be
                        obtained of<lb/>
                        <rs type="title">Whately’s Historic Doubts</rs>). (This article<lb/>can be
                        divided into two – one on Sophistry <lb/>Proper, the other on Curious Proofs
                        and Ar<pc>-</pc><lb/>guments).</item>
                    <item>
                        <rs type="title">Singularities of Language</rs>.</item>
                    <item>(<rs type="title">Historia tragico-Maritima</rs>) (or translate
                        perhaps).</item>
                    <item>
                        <rs type="title">Tobacco / Tobacco in <rs type="place">Portugal</rs></rs>
                        (special) ??? </item>
                    <item>
                        <rs type="title">Freemansonry in <rs type="place">Portugal</rs></rs>
                        (special) ? </item>
                    <item rend="indent-2">
                        <rs type="title">Kings that will Return</rs>. (the general myth of
                        which<lb/>the one of <rs type="name" key="P21">King Sebastian</rs> is a
